http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/Seminar-on-road-safety-held/article13991755.ece

The K.L University on Saturday organised an awareness programme on road accidents and use of safety gears.Deputy Transport Commissioner (Guntur) G.C. Raja Ratnam participated as the chief guest, while MVI N. Siva Nageswara Rao was the resource person at the event. They spoke about road safety mechanisms and suggested measures to avoid the accidents. Dean-Student Affairs Habibulla Khan and Professor N. Srinivasu were among those who took part in the event.Pamphlets on road safety were distributed by Road Transport Department.